1.A token is used to authenticate the user and allow them to receieve specific information that is granted to them.

2.To keep our data secure, we can use authentication to ensure the user has access to the requested information or data transfer.

3.Web servers work by taking in a request, checking to see if that request is authorized, and returning the appropriate information regarding the request.

4.Post, Get, Put, Delete are all mothods for interfacing with APIs/Servers.